== Exercise 4: The model compliance question

In regulated environments, model selection is not purely a technical decision.

Consider: your supervisor uses `gpt-oss-120b` for root cause synthesis.
A compliance auditor asks: "Can you prove this model doesn't hallucinate remediation steps?"

. Review the available models: {litellm_available_models_list}
+
Which are Open Source? Which are Frontier (commercial)?
For a regulated financial services firm, what additional scrutiny applies to Frontier models?

. Review the implications:
+
[cols="1,2",options="header"]
|===
|Model type |Compliance consideration at Meridian Financial

|Open Source (llama-scout-17b, gpt-oss-20b, gpt-oss-120b, qwen3-235b)
|Weights are inspectable. Behavior is reproducible. Can be audited by internal ML team.

|Frontier (gemini-2.5-pro, minimax-m2)
|Closed weights. May have data residency implications. Require additional DPA/vendor review.
|===

. Consider: for which steps in your agent workflow would Meridian Financial's compliance team require OSS-only models?

